The paper deals with algorithms for finding shortest paths in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper also discusses the relationship between the MESP problem and the laminarity problem, which is a topic in graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves approximation algorithms, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
